CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Flash Newspicture Magazine, January 24, 1938, pg. unknown, reads: "John Henry Lewis, the light-heavy-weight boxing champ is venturing into another division, that which is ruled by Dan Cupid, and being a very touch task-master Daniel warns John Henry not to become too, too, enamoured [enamored] over Alice Lindsay Pgh. eye-filler cause love can count you out quicker than Arthur Donovan. Note the champ laying his 'spiel.'  (Photo by 'Teenie' Harris)."
TitMainTitle: Boxer John Henry Lewis leaning in doorway of kitchen, speaking with Alyce or Alice Lindsay in zigzag polka dot dress
